1. PTATDPP - poly{4,8-bis[5-(2-ethylhexyl)thiophen-2-yl]benzo[1,2-b:4,5-b']dithiophene}
2. di-PBI - 3,3'-di(p-butylphenyl)-[1,1'-biphenyl]-4,4'-dicarbonitrile

These are the material names mentioned in the paragraph. PTATDPP is a polymer donor material and di-PBI is a non-fullerene acceptor material in the context of organic photovoltaics.
